<subSubSection id="3EAB6523393CFFD7EF0CFEEC15B0FE13" pageId="11" pageNumber="325" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="760E36A8393CFFD7EF0CFEEC15B0FE13" blockId="11.[831,1437,258,407]" pageId="11" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis id="44C5EABA393CFFD7EF0CFEEC12A9FE9D" bold="true" box="[831,945,258,281]" pageId="11" pageNumber="325">Remarks:</emphasis>
Eaton (1884) already noticed that the 
<typeStatus id="A90A880A393CFFD7E95DFEEC1484FE9D" box="[1390,1436,258,281]" pageId="11" pageNumber="325">type</typeStatus>
was missing in F.-J. Pictet’s collection in 1867. The synonymy proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="12204B59393CFFD7E828FEAF1429FEDC" author="Bae Y. J. &amp; McCafferty W. P." box="[1051,1329,321,344]" pageId="11" pageNumber="325" pagination="1 - 143" refId="ref18475" refString="Bae Y. J., McCafferty W. P. 1991. Phylogenetic systematics of the Potamanthidae (Ephemeroptera). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 117 (3 - 4): 1 - 143." type="journal article" year="1991">Bae &amp; McCafferty (1991)</bibRefCitation>
is consistent with the fact that 
<taxonomicName id="B1B14D2B393CFFD7E802FE8E1595FEF3" baseAuthorityName="Linne" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[1073,1165,352,375]" class="Insecta" family="Potamanthidae" genus="Potamanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteus">
<emphasis id="44C5EABA393CFFD7E802FE8E1595FEF3" box="[1073,1165,352,375]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="325">P. luteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only 
<taxonomicName id="B1B14D2B393CFFD7E93CFE8E1294FE13" class="Insecta" family="Potamanthidae" genus="Potamanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="44C5EABA393CFFD7E93CFE8E1484FEF3" box="[1295,1436,352,375]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="325">Potamanthus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
found throughout Europe.
</paragraph>
